                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14094585" author="daijy" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2014 21:00:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;TestMapSideCogroup works in tez with the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14094592" author="daijy" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2014 21:04:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Similar to MergeJoin(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3647&quot; title=&quot;Implement merge join in Tez&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3647&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3647&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), it uses two DAG:&lt;br/&gt;
DAG 1. Build index for right input&lt;br/&gt;
DAG 2. Do merge cogroup using the index&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095170" author="rohini" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 06:34:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
   TestMergeJoinOuter also needs to be enabled with this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095174" author="daijy" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 06:40:22 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, but that is for merge join, better a separate ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095176" author="rohini" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 06:44:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Few minor comments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;PIG_SPLIT_INDEX should be in PigImplConstants&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Replace occurrences of MRCompilerException with TezCompilerException&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
   Planning to create a enhancement jira to change merge join have the index file broadcasted and picked up from cache similar to replicate join instead of storing to temp location. Do you see any issues with that approach? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095192" author="daijy" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 07:06:22 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Rohini is right. TestMergeJoinOuter does use merge cogroup implementation. New patch enables TestMergeJoinOuter, and also address Rohini&apos;s review comments. Actually there are quite a few MRCompilerException in TezCompiler, fix those as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, we can broadcast index file to improve the performance. Please create a Jira. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095198" author="rohini" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 07:11:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095199" author="daijy" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 07:16:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Rohini for review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095208" author="rohini" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 07:34:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4120&quot; title=&quot;Broadcast the index file in case of POMergeCoGroup and POMergeJoin&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4120&quot;&gt;PIG-4120&lt;/a&gt; for broadcasting the index file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
